summary: This is an email forwarding a voicemail attachment from a DOJ VoIP system to the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS). The email indicates technical issues with automatic forwarding and contains an attached audio file of a voice message from an unavailable caller.

events.title: Voicemail forwarded to US Attorney's Office
events.description: A voicemail message from an unavailable caller was forwarded via email from a DOJ VoIP system to the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.

keyFacts: A voicemail message was forwarded to the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) on July 11, 2019.
The voicemail originated from a DOJ VoIP system (voip.usa.doj.gov) and the caller's name was unavailable.
The email indicates the sender was having technical issues with automatic forwarding of messages.
The attached audio file is named '20190711_143319.wav', suggesting it was recorded at 2:33:19 PM on July 11, 2019.
